The former Master of the High Court in Mpumalanga, Bina Mfandifuna Masuku (44),  appeared in the Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court today. ALSO READ: Fraud-accused former master of the High Court remanded in custody as bail hearing continues Masuku and her co-accused, Elvis Kgosiemang (35), face charges of fraud, corruption and money laundering. The pair had allegedly embezzled funds from deceased estates to the amount of R1,7 million. She also faced an additional charge of contravening the Illegal Immigration Act.  It emerged that Masuku was a Malawian national who had  falsified documents when she submitted her job application to the Department of Justice. The matter was postponed to October 2.